author: mfojtik
msg: Fix long username for RHEVM driver
This patch is to fix a problem with Base64.b64encode for credentials in RHEVM driver, due to a wrong way in pack to add \n every 60 chars i had to use this hack.
The issue is not present in Ruby 1.9.x in fact they use a method called strict_encode64() that is the same as my hack.
